definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image that is a card printed with words, numerals, and/or pictures to be used by an individual or a group as a basis for performing a specific activity. Usually issued in sets. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image that is a card printed with words, numerals, and/or pictures to be used by an individual or a group as a basis for performing a specific activity. Usually issued in sets. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A two-dimensional representation of data in graphic or tabular form (e.g., a wall chart). (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A two-dimensional representation of data in graphic or tabular form (e.g., a wall chart). (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a work in two dimensions or very low relief that were made by affixing paper, fabrics, photographs, or other materials onto a flat surface. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a work in two dimensions or very low relief that were made by affixing paper, fabrics, photographs, or other materials onto a flat surface. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a visual work produced by drawing, which is the application of lines on a surface, often paper, by using a pencil, pen, chalk, or some other tracing instrument to focus on the delineation of form rather than the application of color. This term is often defined broadly to refer to computer-generated images as well. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a visual work produced by drawing, which is the application of lines on a surface, often paper, by using a pencil, pen, chalk, or some other tracing instrument to focus on the delineation of form rather than the application of color. This term is often defined broadly to refer to computer-generated images as well. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A card or other opaque material printed with words, numerals, or pictures and designed for rapid display. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A card or other opaque material printed with words, numerals, or pictures and designed for rapid display. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of an image that portrays a sacred entity and that is itself regarded as sacred. Most commonly comprising tempera on panel, but it may be in any two-dimensional or relief medium, including fresco. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of an image that portrays a sacred entity and that is itself regarded as sacred. Most commonly comprising tempera on panel, but it may be in any two-dimensional or relief medium, including fresco. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of an item in which images are formed primarily by the direct application of pigment suspended in a medium, arranged in masses of color onto a generally two-dimensional surface. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of an item in which images are formed primarily by the direct application of pigment suspended in a medium, arranged in masses of color onto a generally two-dimensional surface. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a card on which a message may be written or printed for mailing without an envelope. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a card on which a message may be written or printed for mailing without an envelope. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a notice, usually decorative or pictorial, intended to be posted to advertise, promote, or publicize an activity, cause, product, or service; also, a decorative, mass-produced print intended for hanging. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a notice, usually decorative or pictorial, intended to be posted to advertise, promote, or publicize an activity, cause, product, or service; also, a decorative, mass-produced print intended for hanging. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a pictorial work produced by transferring an image by means of a matrix such as a plate, block, or screen, using any of various printing processes. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a pictorial work produced by transferring an image by means of a matrix such as a plate, block, or screen, using any of various printing processes. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A photograph produced by the passage of radiation, such as X rays, gamma rays, or neutrons, through an opaque object. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A photograph produced by the passage of radiation, such as X rays, gamma rays, or neutrons, through an opaque object. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a cross section, detail, diagram, elevation, perspective, plan, working plan, etc., made for use in an engineering or other technical context. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: A unit of extent of still image consisting of a cross section, detail, diagram, elevation, perspective, plan, working plan, etc., made for use in an engineering or other technical context. (Deprecated)

ToolkitDefinition_en: Cards or other opaque materials printed with words, numerals, or pictures and designed for rapid display. (Deprecated)

definition[0]_en: Photographs produced by the passage of radiation, such as X rays, gamma rays, or neutrons, through an opaque object. (Deprecated)
ToolkitDefinition_en: Photographs produced by the passage of radiation, such as X rays, gamma rays, or neutrons, through an opaque object. (Deprecated)
